{
  "text": "As noticed in [39, p.99] , the number of dual-perfect points in P n modulo R >0 GL n (Z) is infinite in general. In [CITATION_1] , Berg\u00e9 proved the following: Theorem 2.9 (Berg\u00e9) . The number of dual-extreme points in P n modulo R >0 GL n (Z) is finite. If a \u2208 P n is dual extreme, then there exists \u03bb \u2208 R >0 such that \u03bba \u2208 GL n (Q). In particular , \u03b3 ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "120366486"
